{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "That is, students who have higher previous knowledge prefer to first try coding the task themselves, then they ask ChatGPT for revision or refinement.",
    "On the other hand, students having lower previous knowledge tend to copy-paste entire instruction and get the direct answer from ChatGPT without much engagement.",
    "This finding is supported by previous research (Xia et al., 2023) which reports that students' previous subject matter knowledge can directly influence students' AI interaction.",
    "That is, students with higher prior knowledge can more tend to figure out how to approach a similar problem and how to use available sources (Xia et al., 2023).",
    "This may infer that students who have a certain base in programming fundamentals are more likely to utilize AI tools in a way that complements and extends their capabilities, leading to more effective learning outcomes."
  ],
